            <title>[SOLR-9903] Stop interrupting the update executor on shutdown, it can cause graceful shutdowns to put replicas into Leader Initiated Recovery among other undesirable things.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9903</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I also want this change in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9824&quot; title=&quot;Documents indexed in bulk are replicated using too many HTTP requests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-9824&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-9824&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. There is a related JIRA somewhere that points this out, though that JIRA may be broader in scope.&lt;/p&gt;

